net.majorkernelpanic.streaming
Class Session

java.lang.Object
  net.majorkernelpanic.streaming.Session

public class Session
extends java.lang.Object

This class makes use of all the streaming package. It represents a streaming session between a client and the phone. A stream is designated by the word "track" in this class. To add tracks to the session you need to call addVideoTrack() or addAudioTrack().

addVideoTrack

public Session addVideoTrack(int encoder,
                             int camera,
                             VideoQuality videoQuality,
                             boolean flash)
                      throws java.lang.IllegalStateException,
                             java.io.IOException
Add video track with specified quality and encoder.

Parameters:
encoder - Can be either VIDEO_H264 or VIDEO_H263
camera - Can be either CameraInfo.CAMERA_FACING_BACK or CameraInfo.CAMERA_FACING_FRONT
videoQuality - Will determine the bitrate,framerate and resolution of the stream
flash - Set it to true to turn the flash on, if the phone has no flash, an exception IllegalStateException will be thrown
Throws:
java.lang.IllegalStateException
java.io.IOException
